        "text": "For socially complex problems I then use the Pierson-Meadows [[Nested Questions]]: When, Where, Why, Who, How and finally What. This is done with key stakeholders and requires two to four hours. Once we have a handle on the type and scale of the situation I like to use William Smith's balanced AIC conversation, spending equal time appreciating the whole of the situation, the diverse valuations in the situation based upon stakeholder positions, and finally the design-production-control-implementation conversations. The magic is in keeping the attention on all three domains so that the most [[Power]] possible can be applied to the resolution-creation process.\n"
